 and am desperately seeking\n&gt; followers and fame. And so =\r\non! Logically speaking, based strictly on\n&gt; objective reality perceived by =\r\nphysical senses, none of these conclusions is\n&gt; guaranteed to be correct. T=\r\nhough my true personality is intangible to\n&gt; people, people are looking at =\r\nthe tangible cues from me and constructing\n&gt; notions of who I am, within *t=\r\nheir* minds.\n&gt;\n&gt; *        *        *\n&gt;\n&gt; When someone says &quot;Narasimha is a =\r\ngreat inspiration to people&quot;, one is NOT\n&gt; talking about &quot;me&quot;. One is talki=\r\nng about a character called &quot;Narasimha&quot; that\n&gt; was crated and sustained in =\r\none&#39;s mind by oneself. Though this character was\n&gt; created based on a few t=\r\nangible cues from me, the significant contribution\n&gt; to the creation of thi=\r\ns character was from that person&#39;s own mental\n&gt; conditioning. So this chara=\r\ncter need not even be similar to me! It is a\n&gt; totally different being comp=\r\nared to me and exists/lives only in the mind of\n&gt; that person!\n&gt;\n&gt; When som=\r\neone says &quot;Narasimha is a deluded person&quot;, one is NOT talking about\n&gt; &quot;me&quot;.=\r\n One is talking about a character called &quot;Narasimha&quot; that was crated\n&gt; and =\r\nsustained in one&#39;s mind by oneself. Though this character was created\n&gt; bas=\r\ned on a few tangible cues from me, the significant contribution to the\n&gt; cr=\r\neation of this character was from that person&#39;s own mental conditioning.\n&gt; =\r\nSo this character need not even be similar to me! It is a totally different=\r\n\n&gt; being compared to me and exists/lives only in the mind of that person!\n&gt;=\r\n\n&gt; *        *        *\n&gt;\n&gt; If people say &quot;Narasimha is a great inspiration =\r\nto people&quot; and I am tempted\n&gt; to feel happy, doesn&#39;t it mean I am foolishly=\r\n identifying with a character\n&gt; created and maintained in someone else&#39;s mi=\r\nnd? If people say &quot;Narasimha is a\n&gt; deluded person&quot; and I am tempted to fee=\r\nl unhappy, doesn&#39;t it mean I am\n&gt; foolishly identifying with a character cr=\r\neated and maintained in someone\n&gt; else&#39;s mind? As these characters are crea=\r\nted and maintained in their minds,\n&gt; I have nothing to do with those beings=\r\n and should not identify with them,\n&gt; right?\n&gt;\n&gt; *        *        *\n&gt;\n&gt; To=\r\n make it even more extreme and interesting, I will give another set of\n&gt; sp=\r\necial examples.\n&gt;\n&gt; A few people had dreams in which I met them and told th=\r\nem to do specific\n&gt; types of homam. Some actually started doing homam after=\r\n the dream and some\n&gt; said their lives were transformed after the dream. On=\r\ne person, for example,\n&gt; cleared a tough & important exam after doing badly=\r\n in the mock exams. As I\n&gt; never thought of these people (and did not even =\r\nknow of some of them!), I\n&gt; obviously had no direct influence on the dreams=\r\n they had. The dreams were\n&gt; creations of their own minds. The character ca=\r\nlled &quot;Narasimha&quot; who came in\n&gt; their dreams and transformed their lives, is=\r\n a being built in their own\n&gt; minds. Based on their reading of my writings =\r\nand based on their own mental\n&gt; conditioning, they created a powerful chara=\r\ncter called &quot;Narasimha&quot; in their\n&gt; sub-conscious minds, who is a very good =\r\nsadhaka and guru and having the\n&gt; ability to transform people. That powerfu=\r\nl character (and not me!) came in\n&gt; their dreams and transformed their live=\r\ns!\n&gt;\n&gt; Same thing applies to someone who takes me as guru and becomes reali=\r\nzed.\n&gt; Based on my writings and words and their own mental conditioning, if=\r\n someone\n&gt; succeeds in creating a powerful character called &quot;Narasimha&quot; in =\r\ntheir own\n&gt; mind and lets him affect them positively, they can make great s=\r\npiritual\n&gt; progress. But then, that character is not really me! If someone =\r\nsays &quot;you\n&gt; are my guru&quot;, &quot;you gave me so and so&quot;, &quot;you affected me in so a=\r\nnd so way&quot;, I\n&gt; will understand that a powerful character they constructed =\r\nin their minds,\n&gt; with a little input from me, did all of that!\n&gt;\n&gt; *      =\r\n  *        *\n&gt;\n&gt; Now, one specific example stands out. In this case, the pe=\r\nrson did not know\n&gt; me, never heard of me and did not know of my website. T=\r\nhis person just had a\n&gt; dream in which someone came and said, &quot;I am Narasim=\r\nha Rao. You do so and so\n&gt; homam with so and so mantra&quot; and gave a mantra. =\r\nThis person remembered the\n&gt; dream and did a google search next morning and=\r\n landed on my website. The\n&gt; photo in my website apparently matches the per=\r\nson in the dream. This\n&gt; surprised the person and gave faith.\n&gt;\n&gt; Again, I =\r\nhad no clue and did not know this person at all. So, rationally\n&gt; speaking,=\r\n I had no role to play in this! In this case, this person did not\n&gt; even re=\r\nad my emails or other writings and hence &quot;I&quot; had no direct or\n&gt; indirect ro=\r\nle in the dream. The phenomenon that a character called\n&gt; &quot;Narasimha Rao&quot; w=\r\nas constructed in that person&#39;s sub-conscious mind with\n&gt; some similarities=\r\n with me (looks and spiritual interest) is interesting, but\n&gt; does not mean=\r\n that character is me. Either the person did know about me\n&gt; sometime back =\r\nand forgot (but remembered sub-consciously), or some force up\n&gt; there manip=\r\nulated that mind. In either case, it is not of my doing and the\n&gt; character=\r\n in the dream is a creation of that force and that mind and not me.\n&gt;\n&gt; *  =\r\n      *        *\n&gt;\n&gt; Bottomline is that there are notions in the minds of p=\r\neople who met us in\n&gt; some manner (and possibly even in people who did not =\r\nmeet us), which we may\n&gt; be tempted to identify with and say &quot;that is I&quot;. P=\r\nositive and negative\n&gt; comments on those notional beings give us pride and =\r\nshame, happiness and\n&gt; sadness! How weird!\n&gt;\n&gt; As you cling on to more and =\r\nmore identities, you are stuck more and more.\n&gt; If you think logically and =\r\nimpassionately, you will see that all these\n&gt; characters are someone else&#39;s=\r\n creations and different from you. So they are\n&gt; not &quot;I&quot;. As you drop off o=\r\nne identity after another, you become very light.\n&gt; Your mind becomes very =\r\nclear.\n&gt;\n&gt; *        *        *\n&gt;\n&gt; Now, let us come to a fundamental questi=\r\non. We saw that the notions of\n&gt; &quot;Narasimha&quot; in the minds of people are not=\r\n based on objective reality alone\n&gt; and based on their own conditioning and=\r\n created (and grown over time!) in\n&gt; their own minds! Now, what about the n=\r\notion of &quot;Narasimha&quot; in my own mind?\n&gt; Is that based on objective reality o=\r\nr is it also created (and grown over\n&gt; time!) in my own mind based on my ow=\r\nn conditioning? If so, who is the real\n&gt; &quot;I&quot;?\n&gt;\n&gt; I will let you contemplat=\r\ne on it!\n&gt;\n&gt; Best regards,\n&gt; Narasimha\n&gt; ----------------------------------=\r\n---------------------------------\n&gt;   Free Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish L=\r\nessons, Jyotish Writings,\n&gt; &quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam=\r\n and Pitri Tarpana:\n&gt;                   http://www.VedicAstrologer.org&lt;http=\r\n://www.vedicastrologer.org/&gt;\n&gt;      Films that make a difference: http://Sa=\r\nraswatiFilms.org&lt;http://saraswatifilms.org/&gt;\n&gt;      Spirituality: http://gr=\r\noups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom\n&gt;   Jyotish writings: http://groups.yahoo=\r\n.com/group/JyotishWritings\n&gt;                      Tw