 some of them!), I obviously had no direct influence on the=\r\n dreams they had. The dreams were creations of their own minds. The charact=\r\ner called &quot;Narasimha&quot; who came in their dreams and transformed th=\r\neir lives, is a being built in their own minds. Based on their reading of m=\r\ny writings and based on their own mental conditioning, they created a power=\r\nful character called &quot;Narasimha&quot; in their sub-conscious minds, wh=\r\no is a very good sadhaka and guru and having the ability to transform peopl=\r\ne. That powerful character (and not me!) came in their dreams and transform=\r\ned their lives!&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; s=\r\nize=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;=A0&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=\r\n=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;Same thing applies to someone who =\r\ntakes me as guru and becomes realized. Based on my writings and words and t=\r\nheir own mental conditioning, if someone succeeds in creating a powerful ch=\r\naracter called &quot;Narasimha&quot; in their own mind and lets him affect =\r\nthem positively, they can make great spiritual progress. But then, that cha=\r\nracter is not really me! If someone says &quot;you are my guru&quot;, &quot=\r\n;you gave me so and so&quot;, &quot;you affected me in so and so way&quot;,=\r\n I will understand that a powerful character they constructed in their mind=\r\ns, with a little input from me, did all of that!&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;div align=\r\n=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;=A0&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/d=\r\niv&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;=\r\n&gt;*=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&